ortran/issues/3176/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/3176/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/comments/1907063384","html_url":"https://github.com/lfortran/lfortran/issues/3176#issuecomment-1907063384","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/3176","id":1907063384,"node_id":"IC_kwDOCpMuHc5xq3pY","user":{"login":"kargl","id":28907258,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI4OTA3MjU4","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/28907258?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/kargl","html_url":"https://github.com/kargl","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kargl/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kargl/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kargl/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kargl/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kargl/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kargl/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kargl/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kargl/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/kargl/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-01-23T23:03:02Z","updated_at":"2024-01-23T23:03:02Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"> @kargl I checked 24-007 and it seems the GFortran documentation is pretty good. Do you see anything specific that you would like to improve?

gfortran's documentation for `random_init` should/could be improved.   There are four combinations for `repeatable` and `image_distinct`.  gfortran's doc tries to compress the 24-007 description, and I believe it does a poor job.  It should also have a caveat that `image_distinct` is only relevant if a code uses co-arrays.   If there are no co-arrays or the number of images is 1, then there is obviously only a single executing image; and so, `image_distinct` is meaningless.  (J3 should have made that argument optional.)  gfortran takes advantage of this.

When lfortran gets co-array support, you'll find `random_init(..., .false.)` requires communication between images as all images need to synchronize the seed to initialize the prng of each image.   gfortran punted this to opencoarray.","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/lfortran/lfortran/issues/comments/1907063384/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}}
